race.comment: AUSTMARR (1) should find this more to her liking second up. She was sent around a $3.80 chance first up in stronger company, giving away weight to the likes of Miraval Rose who has won again since, only fading late there to be beaten two lengths and pulling up with mucus which can't have helped. Like her at 1100m with a jumpout between runs, she looks very well placed. HI DUBAI (4) was only beaten by Autumn Glow and Gangsta Granny last time out which is top form. She maps well for Shinn and looks a solid hope. Wary of the filly AKAYSHA (12). The fresh run when just missing My Gladiola is excellent form, and second to Marhoona last time is solid as well. Tough taking on the older mares but she should go well. NEW YORK LUSTRE (5) next best.
